<title type="html"><![CDATA[Maximum wire length between NES and cart]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1829&amp;p=15635#p15635"><![CDATA[
Well, I have made (and am working on another) portable nintendo handheld type thing, and I did notice that sometimes ribbon cables have spotty connection just because they are crimp on connections. I do know you can make it almost as long as you want, but you would need to go about 100 feet or more before anything would probably start to screw up because of that. The length is surely not the issue here. The messing up of sprites is common on faulty NES connectors, make sure you clean both the connectors and carts and make sure your ribbon cables are not bad. Trust me, I have crimped some of my own ribbon cables for projects, and I often mess it up the first time and need to fix it. BTW, good luck with the PC10 project, I hope it goes well.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=450">arfink</a> — Tue Jul 25, 2006 7:42 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
